<L>By &s;ome good-looking gentleman well dre&s;t.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Cecily.</SPEAKER>
<L>Oh! then, I am &s;ure my Dick will &s;peak 'em be&s;t.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Henry Moreland.</SPEAKER>
<L>To win the town the Epilogues intends,</L>
<L>And the play over, plea&s;e our be&s;t of friends.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Zekiel.</SPEAKER>
<L>Plea&s;e our be&s;t friends, that's hearty &s;ure and right.</L>
<L>I &s;py a power here we fain would plea&s;e to night.&mdash;</L>
<L>Who&punc;ll try?&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Dick.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lady Duborly.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Henry Moreland.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Carolina.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Zekiel.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Kenrick.</SPEAKER>
<L>I.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Doctor Panglos</SPEAKER>
<L>And I.&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Kenrick.</SPEAKER>
<L>We're of one mind, had there be twenty 'tis car|ried.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Doctor Panglos.</SPEAKER>
<L>Nemine Di&s;&s;entiente.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Dick.</SPEAKER>
<L>Thus to begin then:&mdash;</L>
<L>If here &s;ome thoughtle&s;s younker may be found,</L>
<L>In fa&s;hions giddy vortex whirling round,</L>
<L>May he to night from Dick's example &s;ee,</L>
<L>That honor's real prop&mdash;is hone&s;ty,&mdash;</L>
<L>May reformation's pledge his cheek o&punc;erca&s;t,</L>
<L>The &s;elf-accu&s;ing blu&s;h for errors pa&s;t&punc;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Cicily.</SPEAKER>
<L>If there's a $a&s;s in love here, $ye, $word$ &s;pied her,</L>
<L>Sitting quite clo&s;e with that young man be&s;ide her,</L>
<L>Let her, like Cecily, to this maxim cling,</L>
<L>Love &s;lights all gold&mdash;except the Wedding Ring.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<PB REF="60">
<SPEAKER>Lord Duberly.</SPEAKER>
<L>Is there ne'er a chandler here&mdash;becau&s;e&mdash;</L>
<L>Old Daniel Dowlas axes his applau&s;e.</L>
<STAGE>[Lady Duberly taps him on the &s;houlder.</STAGE>
<L>Why, zounds&mdash;</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lady Duberly.</SPEAKER>
<L>What&mdash;will you never &s;top,</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Lord Duberly.</SPEAKER>
<L>I'm only axing cu&s;tom for the &s;hop.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Moreland.</SPEAKER>
<L>While filial duty animates each youth,</L>
<L>While virtuous pa&s;&s;ions warms the heart of truth,</L>
<L>With qualities like the&s;e to Britons dear,</L>
<L>Henry may &s;urely hope for favour here.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Caroline.</SPEAKER>
<L>And may not Caroline applau&s;e &s;ecure,</L>
<L>Who to all the&s;e adds feeling for the poor.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Kenrick.</SPEAKER>
<L>Oh bother, there's &s;o many virtues $word$,</L>
<L>There won't be any le&s;t for me, I fear;</L>
<L>Burn him who leaves, I can't &s;ay more or le&s;s,</L>
<L>A patron, friend&punc; or female in di&s;tre&s;s</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Zekiel.</SPEAKER>
<L>$word$ your fi&s;t, that's hearty now and fair,</L>
<L>You be of Zekiel's kidney to a hair.</L>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Doctor Panglos.</SPEAKER>
<L>Does any body want a tutor here,</L>
<L>My terms are but&mdash;three hundred pounds a-year</L>
<L>On their own merits mode&s;t men are dumb&mdash;</L>
<L>Plaudite et Valere.&mdash;<HI>Terence&mdash;Hum!</HI>&mdash;</L>
<L>Then on my merits I &s;hall lay no &s;tre&s;s,</L>
<L>I'm L. L. D. and&mdash;and A. Double S.</L>
</SP>
